	   <a name=103961862617048></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f103961862617048><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=item.html?item=14106&mid=103961862617048>Jerg Oakenfist</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=14106&mid=103961862617048#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=2507><span id=Scholar>Tomlin the Stupendous</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>268 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Dec 11th 10:21 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.53]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I ran into the Jaggedpine earlier tonight, and saw this named treant scooting around... I wasn't really sure if these treants were good or evil though, since they're apprehensive to my halfling druid, and scowl at him when he's in wolf form.<br><br>One of the posts down on this thread said that Jerg Oakenfist was yellow at 52... but I didn't know he was this high in level, since he was just dark blue to me at 57.&nbsp;&nbsp;If I had known he was this high, I probably wouldn't have even considered attacking him, especially by myself!<br><br>The first time, I pulled him with Annul, though I'm not really sure why; it was probably because he appeared to have a run speed buff, and I assumed he would have other buffs on as well.  I snared him, and tried to root him so I could throw a couple dots on him... but he was casting some spells on me, and root wasn't working very well, so this eventually turned into a nasty kite with me zoning out at 20% hp and 20% mana.<br><br>While I sat in Surefall Glade, regaining my mana and health... and my wits, I formulated a plan to kill him.  With my buffs still good, I zoned back into Jaggedpine with full health and about 80% mana.  I tracked down Jerg, to see where he was, and once I found him, I began tracking around for a giant anaconda.  These snakes are still dark blue to me at 57, and they're animals, so I was going to use them to kill this treant.  I found the snake, snared him for safety, then used Glamour of Tunare to help Call of Karana work a bit better.  Then I hasted him with Savage Spirit, the level 44 druid pet buff.  Next, I dragged him along until I found Jerg again, and sent the snake in to attack.  The snake was doing a lot of damage, I'm sure, since those things hit very hard, and he had a good haste buff on... but Oakenfist was extremely durable.  I think he dispelled the charm on the anaconda, because the charm broke after he had cast something, so I backed off a ways, and recharmed the snake.  After a few rounds, Jerg began to attack the snake again... and eventually killed it.  Now Jerg had about 40% of his health left, but he started casting heals on himself, and as a druid, I had very limited ability to stun him and stop his spells... so he healed up some, and came lumbering after me.  By now, I was low on health, and low on mana, and trying to kill this tree... so I tracked down another giant anaconda, and dragged Jerg over towards it.  When I finally found the snake, I used the same tactics... snare, tash, charm, attack tree.  Now I was running around in large circles, with Jerg following me around, and the snake attacking him... this went on for a couple of minutes.  Next, I told the snake to stay put, and pulled Jerg away from it a bit, then circled back around to drop a haste buff on the snake, so he could do more damage to the treant.  The whole time, Jerg was sporadically stopping to heal himself.  Eventually, after I spent a few more minutes running around frantically dodging various griffs that were zooming about, Jerg Oakenfist fell silent.<br><br>Lost faction with Treants of Jaggedpine.<br>Lost faction with Residents of Jaggedpine.<br><br>Jerg Oakenfist dropped three items:<br><br>Oakenfist Gloves<br>Gnollish Holy Symbol (NO RENT)<br>Gnoll Warrior Crest (NO RENT)<br><br>I came here trying to find out what these items were for, but since time is short, I'll have to log back in and beg somebody to kill me to preserve these things until I can find out what they're for.<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Wed Dec 11 11:37:05 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
