	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Dec 11th 11:55 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.61]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Okay, here's what I remember about Jerg Oakenfist...<br><br>It may be obvious, but I'll say it anyway:&nbsp;&nbsp;he's a druid.  Now, I didn't quite understand his casting methods... and I didn't like the way he cheated, either!  He was hitting for around 150 or so in melee, so I assumed he was around level 50 or maybe even a few levels higher... which is why his spellcasting didn't make any sense.  A few times, he was chain-casting the level 34 druid spell Fury of Air on me; this was where the cheating came in.  Fury of Air has a pretty fast casting time, does 250 magic damage, and stuns for about 2.0 seconds... and it also has a recast delay around 30 seconds or so.  However, he was casting it over and over and over, several times in a row, like it was a regular spell; he *almost* kept me perpetually stunned when I couldn't resist the spell a few times in a row.  Also, he was casting a fire nuke that did 184 damage... making me combust?  Combust is the level 29 druid fire nuke... why is a level 50+ druid casting that?  He was also using Drones of Doom, instead of Drifting Death or Winged Death.  He never bothered to throw a snare spell my way, or a root spell either, that I can remember.<br><br>In melee, he was hitting me for up to 150 damage or so.  He's a pretty big tree, so his melee range is pretty far too, similar to a giant.  I couldn't even begin to guess at his health total:  the giant anacondas generally hit for over 100, and my pets were hasted (45% or so I think) most of the time, so they were tearing him up pretty bad... and I had to use two different snakes to kill him!  I had used my sleeves to put Drones of Doom on him a few times while I ran him around, and I managed to land Winged Death on him a couple of times as well.  To put it simply, Jerg Oakenfist is one very resilient tree.<br><br>As far as where to find him... I'm guessing that he's just a random spawn from the treant cycle.  When I first found him, he was scooting around near the human outpost... but later, when I tracked him down for the final battle, he was pretty far away from the outpost, and I ended up running him near the bandit camp at one point.  This was probably because I was dragging him behind me, while I searched for another anaconda to charm.  I don't really have any information on his spawn, but if I had to suggest something, I would say to kill the treants in the zone until he showed up.<br><br>Also, if anyone happens to learn of a quest involving these gnoll relics, please post it here somewhere.  <img src=/ubbnew/graemlins/smile.gif><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
